---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="Linear Algebra" favicon="📐">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">← back to reading</a>

    <h1>📐 Linear Algebra</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-2">Based on <a href="https://hefferon.net/linearalgebra/">Jim Hefferon's <em>Linear Algebra</em></a>, licensed <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/fdl-1.3.html">GFDL</a> + <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.5/">CC BY-SA 2.5</a>.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">Five chapters from systems of equations to eigenvalues. Runnable Python, SVG diagrams, plain English.</p>

    <!-- SVG: 2D vector space with two basis vectors and a linear combination -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 280" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Grid lines -->
        <line x1="30" y1="240" x2="330" y2="240" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="180" x2="330" y2="180" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="120" x2="330" y2="120" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="30" y1="60" x2="330" y2="60" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="90" y1="20" x2="90" y2="260" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="150" y1="20" x2="150" y2="260" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="210" y1="20" x2="210" y2="260" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <line x1="270" y1="20" x2="270" y2="260" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <!-- Origin -->
        <circle cx="90" cy="240" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.3"/>
        <!-- Basis vector e1 (blue) -->
        <line x1="90" y1="240" x2="207" y2="240" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" stroke-opacity="0.7"/>
        <polygon points="210,240 200,235 200,245" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="155" y="258" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13" font-style="italic">e₁</text>
        <!-- Basis vector e2 (amber) -->
        <line x1="90" y1="240" x2="90" y2="123" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="2" stroke-opacity="0.7"/>
        <polygon points="90,120 85,130 95,130" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="75" y="178" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="13" font-style="italic">e₂</text>
        <!-- Linear combination v = 2e1 + e2 (green, dashed components) -->
        <line x1="90" y1="240" x2="270" y2="240" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
        <line x1="270" y1="240" x2="270" y2="120" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
        <!-- Result vector v -->
        <line x1="90" y1="240" x2="266" y2="124" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="2" stroke-opacity="0.8"/>
        <polygon points="270,120 258,122 262,132" fill="#34d399" fill-opacity="0.8"/>
        <text x="285" y="115" text-anchor="start" fill="#34d399" font-size="13" font-style="italic">v</text>
        <!-- Label -->
        <text x="280" y="85" text-anchor="start" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.4">v = 2e₁ + e₂</text>
        <!-- Caption -->
        <text x="180" y="275" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.35">Every vector is a linear combination of basis vectors.</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Chapter</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-01/">1. Linear Systems</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Row reduction turns any system of equations into echelon form, making solutions obvious</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-01/">📐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-02/">2. Vector Spaces</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Subspaces, linear independence, basis, and dimension — the vocabulary for everything that follows</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-02/">📐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-03/">3. Maps Between Spaces</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Homomorphisms are structure-preserving maps, and every one of them is a matrix in disguise</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-03/">📐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-04/">4. Determinants</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">A single number that tells you whether a matrix is invertible and how it scales volume</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-04/">📐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-05/">5. Similarity</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Eigenvalues, eigenvectors, and Jordan form — choosing the basis that makes a map simplest</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/hefferon-05/">📐</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>


    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8">📺 Video lectures: <a href="https://www.3blue1brown.com/topics/linear-algebra">3Blue1Brown: Essence of Linear Algebra</a></p>

    <h3>Neighbors</h3>
    <ul class="neighbors">
      <li><a href="/reading/machine-learning/">🤖 Machine Learning</a> &mdash; linear regression, PCA, and neural networks are linear algebra in disguise</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/calculus/">∫ Calculus</a> &mdash; multivariable calculus runs on vectors and matrices</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/abstract-algebra/">🔗 Abstract Algebra</a> &mdash; vector spaces are modules over a field</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/geometry/">△ Geometry</a> &mdash; transformations and dot products connect</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/control/">🎛 Control Theory</a> &mdash; state space representation is matrix algebra</li>
    </ul>

  </main>
</Layout>
